===Etymology===
Short form of ''[[pianoforte]]'', from {{etyl|it}} {{term|piano||soft|lang=it}} + {{term|forte||strong|lang=it}}. So named because older keyboard instruments, notably the [[harpsichord]] and the [[clavier]], could not produce varied volumes.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{musical instruments}} A [[keyboard]] [[musical]] [[instrument]], usually ranging over seven [[octave]]s, with white and black keys, played by pressing these keys, causing [[hammer]]s to strike [[string]]s.

